g experience\r\n\r\n• PYP teaching experience preferred for Early Childhood and Elementary Classes\r\n\r\n\r\nEducation/Certification:\r\n\r\n• Bachelor\'s or Master\'s degree in Education preferred\r\n\r\n• Teaching certification from an accredited institution\r\n\r\n\r\nAge:\r\n\r\n• Under 60 years of age. Government will not issue work visa to anyone over the age of 60.',0,0,0,0,0,0,1,108,NULL,'2019-11-25 09:43:12','2019-11-25 09:43:12'),(40,'English Teacher (Primary School)',78,'2020-08-25',1,0,'310000','310100',1,1,'1','',1,'','8:30 5:00','No More Than 20 Hours','19','',3,'Under 60 Years of Age',2,1,'',2,0,1,15000,25000,'0',0,1,1,'0',0,1,1,'All National Holidays and Summer and Winter Vacations',1,'',0,1,0,'Job Description:\r\n\r\nYK Pao School is committed to safeguarding and promoting the welfare of children and expects all staff and volunteers to share this commitment. References, background checks and criminal record checks will be required.\r\n\r\nJob Description:\r\n\r\nPrimary/Elementary school teacher. YK Pao School is a unique bilingual school in Shanghai, offering a blended Shanghai and bespoke International curriculum. Students are immersed in a two way Chinese and English programme (with co-teaching in some subjects) and teachers are required to teach fewer subjects than in a more traditional International/Western educational setting. We are currently seeking experienced and innovative educators who preferably have some experience of bilingual education to join us for the 2020-2021 Academic year.\r\n\r\n\r\nKey Responsibilities:\r\n\r\n1. Teaching and Learning\r\n\r\na. Plan, teach and evaluate classes as designated by subject coordinators;\r\nb. Ensure that teaching and learning is aligned with the school’s bespoke curriculum model;\r\nc. Set up reasonable proximal goals for students based on curriculum requirements; teach students in accordance with their aptitude;\r\nd. Differentiate learning to cater for full range of student needs to ensure they are engaged and challenged;\r\ne. Use technology to enhance learning and help students develop the necessary skills and confidence in this area;\r\nf. Organize related activities outside of the classroom to enhance student learning and development;\r\ng. Respect the bi-lingual environment and cater to language needs of both native and second language learners;\r\nh. Communicate proactively with colleagues and parents regarding students’ learning;\r\n\r\n2. Classroom and Behavior management\r\n\r\na. Develop a close and supportive relationship with students under your care; establish a rapport which enhances learning;\r\nb. Help deliver the pastoral programme (Character Education, Positive Discipline);\r\nc. Be a positive role model for all students in the school and recognize your responsibility for their well-being and development;\r\nd. Establish a classroom environment where students feel safe and comfortable to take risks;\r\ne. Ensure that classroom/school resources are well prepared and managed;\r\nf. Implement and ensure students follow the School’s behavior policy;\r\ng. Ensure that all students are treated equitably with respect and fairness;\r\nh. Acknowledge children’s improvement and effort rather than just result or achievement;\r\n\r\n3. Relationship management\r\n\r\na. Work co-operatively and supportively with other staff;\r\nb. Share information, ideas and resources with colleagues and line managers in the best interests of students;\r\nc. Build trusting, collaborative and respectful working relationship with parents in order to co-educate students;\r\n\r\n4. Administrative Duties\r\n\r\na. Fulfill the administrative functions of classroom management e.g. attendance, routines, absences\r\nb. Ensure assessment data is shared and archived;\r\nc. Communicate in a timely fashion with parent/caregivers regarding student learning and well-being;\r\n\r\n5. Contribution to Wider School Life\r\n\r\na. Uphold and fulfil the school’s professional standards;\r\nb. Support and uphold the school’s excellent reputation in the wider community;\r\nc. Fulfil the school ethos by focusing on whole person education, internationalism appreciation of Chinese culture;\r\n\r\n\r\nJob requirements:\r\n\r\n1. Bachelors of Education or PGCE and a degree in the subject area that you teach\r\n2. 2+ years teaching experience in full-time school\r\n3. International experience\r\n4. Bilingual \\ Bicultural teaching experience is preferred\r\n5. Teaching qualification\r\n6. Native English (for international staff)\r\n7. Excellent communication skills\r\n8. Proficiency in/knowledge of a second language (desirable)\r\n9. Team player\r\n10. Flexible and adaptable',0,0,0,0,0,0,1,108,NULL,'2019-11-25 12:59:00','2019-11-25 12:59:00'),(41,'MS Computer Teacher',76,'2020-01-26',1,0,'310000','310100',1,1,'10','',3,'','8:00-4:15','No More Than 20 Hours Per Week','19','',3,'Under 60 Years of Age',2,2,'',2,0,1,15000,25000,'0',0,1,1,'0',0,1,1,'All National Holidays + Summer & Winter Vacations',1,'',0,1,0,'SUMMARY\r\nUnder the direction and supervision of the Principal, provides educational leadership and instruction for the students.  Supervises teaching assistants, volunteers, and students and provides hands-on learning environment for optimum student growth. Attends school and department division meetings, utilizes web as a classroom resource and for communication. Assesses and reports assigned student activities, projects, and homework. Other duties as assigned.\r\n\r\nPRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES\r\n1. Supervise and educate students, utilize teaching assistants and volunteer parents, attend meetings and report to administration.      \r\n2. Supervise and educate students.\r\n3. Prepare materials for lessons, presentations, labs, projects, concerts, and learning \r\n4. centers.\r\n5. Maintain hard copy and electronic filing system of student attendance and grades. \r\n6. Supervise delegated assignments to TAs (teaching assistants) or volunteers.\r\n7. Follow Common Core curriculum (www.cde.ca.gov) and develop lessons based around these standards.\r\n8. Setup and coordinate meetings with parents during parent-teacher conferences and as needed. \r\n9. Attend department and staff-wide meetings.\r\n10. Answer emails and phone calls and handle in an appropriate manner within 24 hours receipt. \r\n11. Meet and greet visitors and prospective parents. \r\n12. Use internal postal system for incoming and outgoing letters and packages.\r\n13. Write purchase orders for school supplies, equipment, or furniture, complete work orders when repairs needs to be made, fill out incident for verbal or physical fights or disputes, and accident reports when staff or students are injured, field trips requests, and time off sheets. \r\n14. Coordinate project-based work. \r\n15. Participate in school events such as orientations, open houses, plays, concerts, science fairs, field trips, PTSA meetings, etc.\r\n16. Perform classroom website updates and act as school’s communication rep from administration to parents and students.\r\n17. Take pictures and maintain anecdotal notes, written observations,\r\n18. and other approved forms of documentation for each child.\r\n19. Attend all school sponsored events with duties assigned relating to and interacting with students, staff and LAS families.\r\n20. All full time instructional staff are required to sponsor at least one after school club.  Extra pay will be provided for time dedicated for sponsor duties.\r\n21. Other duties as assigned. \r\n\r\nCURRICULUM DEVELOPMENT and PLANNING AND PREPARATION\r\n1. Oversee the development, implementation, and monitoring of a comprehensive subject area action plan for each phase of the curriculum cycle including curriculum assessment, program support, co-and extra-curricular activities, and staff development.\r\n2. Participate in the planning activities in the subject area related to its placement on the curriculum cycle.\r\n3. Facilitate grade level/subject planning and assessment.\r\n4. Participate in the planning and facilitating of student activities to support instructional practice.\r\n5. Implement to fidelity adopted curriculum and program support.\r\n6. Revise instructional materials based on current research and department/school philosophy, utilizing the web-based Atlas curriculum mapping tool. \r\n\r\nPROGRAM EVALUATION\r\n1. Gather and analyze classroom student’s evidence about the quality of the school program with respect to the criteria and the expected school-wide learning results.\r\n2. Coordinate data gathering and analysis and reporting the result of self-study for the purpose of developing an action plan.\r\n3. Develop an action plan for program improvement.\r\n\r\nADDITIONAL RESPONSIBILITIES \r\n1. Ability to speak English at native or fluent levels. (Chinese, Japanese, Korean, Tagalog etc optional)\r\n2. Ability to update the class website and information boards,\r\n3. Ability to organize and maintain in confidence sensitive school data.\r\n4. Be aware of all activities on campus and be able to contact anyone for completion of Principal assigned tasks.\r\n5. Be able to trouble shoot under given parameters from administration.\r\n\r\nKNOWLEDGE AND SKILL REQUIREMENTS \r\nBachelors’ degree in related field.\r\nTeaching license or equivalent.\r\n2 years experience teaching in an accredited school preferred.\r\nKnowledge of Microsoft Office and telephone protocol. Computer literate with the \r\nability to learn new software applications. Duties require professional verbal and \r\nwritten communication skills and the ability to type. Visibility of work requires \r\nattention to detail, excellent organizational skills, and discretion with confidential \r\ninformation.\r\n\r\nWORKING CONDITIONS\r\nWorking conditions are normal for a school executive’s office environment. Work may require occasional overnight travel and weekend and/or evening work.',0,0,0,0,0,0,1,108,NULL,'2019-11-25 16:44:02','2019-11-25 16:4