in the northeast of Anhui province. Bengbu city is connected by mountains and rivers with four distinct seasons. It has a long history and splendid culture. As the ancient Bengbu rich mussels, hence the name \"pearl city\".\r\nBengbu city is located in the middle reaches of Huaihe river, An important comprehensive transportation hub in the country. It has three airports, Bengbu south station is one of the seven passenger stations along the Beijing-Shanghai high-speed railway. So the transportation here is very convenient. It takes about 35 minutes from Bengbu to Nanjing by bullet train.\r\nIt has many scenic spots and historic sites, such as the Ming imperial tombs, Zhongdu city and Longxing temple in the east. It has a pleasant climate and you will have a pleasant life here.','<h1><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">Bengbu&nbsp; </span></strong><br/></h1><p><a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Bengbu Map\" class=\"clsphotogalleryimg singleImg_noDesp\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/map/anhui/china-anhui-map-s.gif\" style=\"margin: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(209, 209, 209); padding: 5px; float: right;\" width=\"237\" height=\"320\"/></a></p><div class=\"subTitle2017\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\">Bengbu Facts</h2></div><p>Chinese Name: 蚌埠市 (bèng bù shì)<br/>Population: 3,524,700<br/>Area: 5,952 square kilometers (2,298 square miles)<br/>Nationalities: Han<br/><br/>Location: Situated in the north of <a href=\"http://undefined\">Anhui Province</a>, Bengbu is bordered by <a href=\"http://undefined\">Huainan City</a> in the south and neighbors <a href=\"http://undefined\">Jiangsu Province</a> in the east. The Huaihe River flows through the southern part of the city&#39;s territory.</p><p><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191129/5a3c9a016ed01dce79fcbb4b153ee3cf.jpg\"/></p><p>Administrative Division: 4 districts (Bengshan, Longzihu, Yuhui, Huaishang); 3 counties (Huaiyuan, Wuhe, Guzhen)</p><div class=\"subTitle2017BG\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\"><strong>Attractions</strong></h2></div><div><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/>&nbsp;Longzi Lake<br/>Located\r\n in the eastern suburb of&nbsp;Bengbu, Longzi Lake Scenic Area is composed of\r\n Longzi Lake, Xuehua Mountain, Caoshan Mountain, Xilu Mountain and \r\nZhuizi Mountain. Covering an area of eleven square miles, with over one \r\nthird of it being the water area, Longzi Lake Scenic Area is famous for \r\nbreathtaking natural scenery as well as rich historical relics<br/>Longzi\r\n Lake has an indented coastline and deep water. It is surrounded by \r\nmountains on three sides. The undulating Zhuizi Mountain and Caoshan \r\nMountain lie on the eastern coast. To the west, Meihua Mountain and \r\nXuehua Mountain are covered with patches of green trees. To the south, \r\nthere are nine channels which are the source of Longzi Lake<br/>Moreover,\r\n Longzi Lake Scenic Area has many historical relics such as an ancient \r\ngingko tree from the Tang Dynasty (618-907), the tomb of Tang He (a \r\ngreat general in Ming Dynasty (1368 - 1644)), Xiyan Temple relic and \r\nLinglong Pagoda Relic</p><p><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191129/a523e82d95ed6199f13c4887b666c8aa.jpg\"/></p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/>&nbsp;White Milk Spring (Bairu Spring<br/>Lodged\r\n between Jingshan Mountain and Huai River, in the south Huaiyuan County \r\nsuburbs, White Milk Spring gets the name after its milk white spring \r\nwater. The spring sprouts gushing mineral-rich water all seasons in the \r\ncenter of Chunyang Temple. It was once called Baigui (White Tortoise) \r\nSpring, when people sighted a white tortoise emerges from the spring. \r\nWanghuai Tower stands on the left side of the spring and Shuanglie \r\nTemple stands on the right side. The place is beautiful and tranquil. \r\nThe spring water is suitable for making tea.</p><div class=\"subTitle2017BG\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\">Transportation</h2></div><p>Its\r\n passenger transport west station and the east station as well as the \r\nFeiyan express bus station are all located in the Huaihai Road of the \r\ndowntown area. The city is about two hours&#39; drive to <a href=\"http://undefined\">Nanjing</a> and only a bit more than an hour&#39;s ride to the capital city of Anhui Province, <a href=\"http://undefined\">Hefei</a>.<br/>Bengbu\r\n Railway Station is about 2 kilometers (1.2 miles) to downtown area. It \r\nhas trains to/from about 45 cities, such as Shanghai, Nanjing, Beijing, \r\nSuzhou, Hangzhou, and Xi&#39;an. Bengbu South Railway Station mainly \r\noperates high-speed trains to/from Beijing, Shanghai, Changsha, \r\nGuangzhou and more majoy domestic cities.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/> See more <a href=\"http://undefined\">Shanghai - Bengbu Train</a><br/></p></div><p><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Bengbu Tenghu Airport</a><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;is\r\n under construction now, and about 37 kilometers (23 miles) away from \r\nthe center of Bengbu. Currently, visitors can transfer at&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Hefei Xinqiao International Airport</a><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">Nanjing Lukou International Airport</a><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">, then go to Bengbu by train or intercity shuttle bus.</span></p><p><span style=\"text-align: justify;\">Weather<br/></span></p><p>Bengbu\r\n lies between the subtropical humid monsoon climatic zone and temperate \r\nsemi-humid monsoon climatic zone, enjoying features of both climatic \r\ntypes. Weather in spring is unstable, and winter dry and cold. Plum rain\r\n period will last about twenty days during late June to mid-July<br/><span class=\"td0b\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/>&nbsp;</span>When to Go: spring and summer&nbsp;</p><div class=\"subTitle2017BG\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\">Bengbu Travel Tips</h2></div><p><span class=\"td0b\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/>&nbsp;</span>History:\r\n In prehistorical period, this region was inhabited by groups of tribes.\r\n Its present territory partly belonged to several states and kingdoms \r\nbefore the Qin Dynasty (221BC-206BC) unified China. Since then, the city\r\n was under the administration of the shires and prefectures in this \r\narea<br/><span class=\"td0b\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/>&nbsp;</span>Physical\r\n Features: Situated at the juncture of the Jianghuai Hilly Region and \r\nthe Jianghuai Plain,&nbsp;Bengbu belongs to the alluvial plain area. Its \r\nterrain declines from the south to the north with gentle rolls<br/><span class=\"td0b\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-arrow1.png\" width=\"17\" height=\"12\"/>&nbsp;</span>Special Local Products: megranate of Huaiyuan County, crab of the Tuohu Lake, stone carving teapot of Guxian Count<br/>In\r\n the busiest downtown area, there is an antique and jade market located \r\nin the east end of the Nanshan Road. Rosewood furniture, antique and \r\njade wares can be found in this large-scaled trading center. It also has\r\n an exhibition hall in the second floor, displaying various collections \r\nand handicrafts.</p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:19px\">What is the realistic cost of living in Bengbu, including rent?</span></strong></p><p><span>Apartments (not shared) range from 700 RMB to 3000 RMB.</span></p><p><span>10 RMB to 30 RMB for one inexpensive meal.</span></p><p><span>1 RMB or 2 RMB for buses within the city limit.</span></p><p><span>Electricity and water are prepaid. Together it may cost around 100 RMB per month..</span></p><p><span>Internet fee is around 100 RMB per month.</span></p><p><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191129/71d9a3de1874507d7ad2c749ce586dcb.gif\"/></p>','2019-11-01','52140700MJ1752764B','办学许可证','2018-11-05','2021-11-05','徐扬华','340826197603155616','刘思轶','86','15955286210','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191101/ac529bf83ab1b234157528668717c66b.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191101/2c51469b82dbd30a12b0408180aebcc5.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/ed1929748eb937639e27bdd48f02574d.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/24b8841999ac33ab3c9210448c8769ef.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/24b8841999ac33ab3c9210448c8769ef.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/6a99fab2f7fa193dd29eaea339c59d98.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/c54dc2315b1dc57c47a6bf9b190c1dd2.jpg',0,0,0,33,NULL,'2019-11-01 02:50:32','2019-12-03 01:58:02'),(27,58,'Anshun Peiwen school of Peking university','',1,1,3,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191125/dd41cda8e1c03ad4e5a9c4669bcde65a.png','','','Anshun Peiwen school of Peking university is an elite private boarding school integrating elementary school, junior high school, high school and international communication center. It was found by the joint efforts of Peking University, YanGo Education Group and Beichen Zhengfang Group, supported by the local government. (http://www.pkuas.com/) The school is located in Anshun, covering an area of 203 acres, with a total construction area of nearly 100,000 square meters. Surrounded by the government and bus station that provides a rich cultural atmosphere.','520000','520400','榆次区中都北路与文津街交汇处','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191101/04e59c9e337795b855e6d13a832254b4.jpg','The opening position now is in Anshun City. Anshun is a prefecture-level city under the jurisdiction of Guizhou Province. It is located in the Midwest of Guizhou Province, which is the hometown of waterfall, a national excellent tourist city in south central Guizhou, China. It is close to Xixiu district government and Anshun east bus station. So the transportation here is very convenient. Anshun nown as \"waterfall town of China\", it is an excellent tourist city in China. The climate of Anshun is mainly characterized by cool, moist and mild climate. Anshun has two AAAAA national scenic spots -- Huangguoshu Waterfalls Scenic Area and LOONG PALACE.','<h1>Anshun&nbsp; Guide</h1><p><a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Anshun Map\" class=\"clsphotogalleryimg singleImg_noDesp\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/map/guizhou/guizhou-s.gif\" style=\"margin: 5px; border: 1px solid rgb(209, 209, 209); padding: 5px; float: right;\" width=\"294\" height=\"320\"/></a>Situated to the east of Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau in the mid-western part of <a href=\"http://undefined\">Guizhou Province</a>,\r\n Anshun City has become the center of tourism for the western part of \r\nGuizhou. Located directly on the route between Qian (Guizhou) and Dian \r\n(Yunnan), it has been the collection and distribution center for \r\ncommercial goods since ancient times. Due to its important strategic \r\nposition, it is also known as - &#39;the belly of Qian, the throat of Dian, \r\nthe lips and teeth of Shu (Sichuan) and Yue (Guangdong)&#39;<br/>There \r\nis one district (Xixiu District), two counties (Pingba County, Puding \r\nCounty), and three autonomous counties (Guanling Buyi Minority and Miao \r\nMinority Autonomous County, Zhenning Buyi and Miao Minority Autonomous \r\nCounty, and Ziyun Miao Minority and Buyi Minority Autonomous County) \r\nunder Anshun City&#39;s governance<br/></p><div class=\"subTitle2017\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\"><a href=\"http://undefined\">Attractions</a></h2></div><p>Many\r\n beautiful mountains and rivers decorate this mysterious land. Three \r\nnational scenic and historic interest areas are located here including: <a href=\"http://undefined\">Huangguoshu Waterfall National Park</a> (National AAAAA Level), <a href=\"http://undefined\">Dragon Palace Cave Scenic Spot</a>\r\n (National AAAAA Level), and Getu River Scenic Area. The&nbsp;city also hosts\r\n one national forest park, Jiulongshan Forest Park, as well as a number \r\nof province-level and city-level scenic spots<br/>The spectacular \r\nscenery of this area is most often associated with the typical Karst \r\ntype of topography. In addition to the scenery, there are many notable \r\nhistoric places of interest that leave an everlasting mark on visitors \r\nincluding: Puding Chuandong Human Fossil Site renowned as &#39;Asian Lamp of\r\n Civilization&#39;, the &#39;Red Cliff Relics&#39; - one of the eight mysterious \r\nwritings in China - a book from Heaven, <a href=\"http://undefined\">Anshun Wenmiao Temple</a> - renowned for stone-carving building complex, <a href=\"http://undefined\">Tun Bu Village</a>,\r\n cliffside inscriptions, ancient rock art, and ancient tombs. With so \r\nmany places to visit,&nbsp;it has become a well known tourist resort.</p><table style=\"margin: 0px auto;\" border=\"0\" align=\"center\">	<tbody>		<tr>			<td>			<table class=\"tableInPic\" align=\"left\">				<tbody>					<tr>						<td align=\"center\"><img alt=\"Huangguoshu Waterfall, Anshun \" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/photogallery/2010/guizhou-huangguoshu-waterfall.jpg\" style=\"display: block;\" width=\"320\" height=\"226\"/></td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td style=\"background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239); padding: 10px 5px;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Huangguoshu Waterfall </span></td>					</tr>				</tbody>			</table>			</td>			<td>			<table class=\"tableInPic\" align=\"left\">				<tbody>					<tr>						<td align=\"center\"><img alt=\"Dragon Palace Cave, Anshun, Guizhou\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/photogallery/0016500/anshun guizhou 10016179tm.jpg\" style=\"display: block;\" width=\"320\" height=\"226\"/></td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td style=\"background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239); padding: 10px 5px;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Dragon Palace Cave</span></td>					</tr>				</tbody>			</table>			</td>		</tr>	</tbody></table><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/logo/ico/hot2.gif\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\"/>&nbsp;Recommended Tour including the visit to Anshun:<br/><a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\">Yunnan-Guizhou Minorities</a>: 10 days, Kunming, Lijiang, Huangguoshu Waterfall and other Yunnan and Guizhou cities.</p><div class=\"subTitle2017BG\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\"><a href=\"http://undefined\">How to get to/around Anshun</a></h2></div><p>Due\r\n to the Anshun&#39;s important position in the history of Guizhou,&nbsp;it was \r\nthe earliest development area in Guizhou. Today, getting to and from&nbsp;the\r\n area&nbsp;is very convenient since the Qingzhen - Huangguoshu Speedway and <a href=\"http://undefined\">Anshun Huangguoshu Airport</a> are both open for travelers. Thus a pleasant trip to Anshun should be no problem.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><table style=\"margin: 0px auto;\" border=\"0\" align=\"center\">	<tbody>		<tr>			<td>			<table class=\"tableInPic\" align=\"left\">				<tbody>					<tr>						<td align=\"center\"><img alt=\"Girls of Miao Minority \" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/photogallery/2010/guizhou-miao-minority.jpg\" style=\"display: block;\" width=\"320\" height=\"226\"/></td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td style=\"background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239); padding: 10px 5px;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Girls of Miao Minority </span></td>					</tr>				</tbody>			</table>			</td>			<td>			<table class=\"tableInPic\" align=\"left\">				<tbody>					<tr>						<td align=\"center\"><img alt=\"Old Han Minority People in Anshun\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/photogallery/0016500/10016493tm.jpg\" style=\"display: block;\" width=\"320\" height=\"226\"/></td>					</tr>					<tr>						<td style=\"background-color: rgb(239, 239, 239); padding: 10px 5px;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Old Han Minority People</span></td>					</tr>				</tbody>			</table>			</td>		</tr>	</tbody></table><p><a href=\"http://undefined\">Dining</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href=\"http://undefined\">Shopping &amp; Nightlife</a></p><p>The\r\n city&nbsp;is a cultural melting pot with contributions from the Miao, Buyi \r\nand Gelao minority groups. These citizens are proud of the diverse mix \r\nof cultures which may be seen in: architecture styles - Folk House of \r\nGuizhou Tunbao; festivals - Tiaohua Festival, Baishu Festival, Ox King \r\nFestival, Changxin Festival; ethnic arts &amp; crafts - brocade, wax \r\nprinting, kitchen knife, embroidery; finery and decorations; and their \r\nspecial local foods and snacks- crystal bean jelly, glutinous rice cake,\r\n Zhenning Bobo Candy. The Living Fossil of Drama - Di Opera at Anshun of\r\n Guizhou is another &quot;must-see&quot; during your visit.</p>','2018-12-12','52520402MJY309797W','办学许可证','2018-09-01','2023-08-31','徐扬华','340826197603155616','熊洪波','86','17785632195','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191101/da37b44ce27bbb0bb9f95833b621defa.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191101/71d51babd7712d3708e95ec62a162e42.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/ed1929748eb937639e27bdd48f02574d.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/f397edea93b878a4453b4adb0763cac5.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/f397edea93b878a4453b4adb0763cac5.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/6c581e2ee2a486a9e1121d8a835ae33a.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191108/d91a5546f15eb3aa6b2af5e312abd2e1.png',0,0,0,33,NULL,'2019-11-01 03:19:37','2019-11-25 06:25:18'),(28,111,'UBS','',2,3,0,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191111/5753b73b7475203a4c84738b75d1c889.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191113/811cda8dc5c95baaf6a98b3d439c5206.mp4','','UBS works with individuals, families, institutions, and corporations around the world to help answer some of life\'s questions – whether through award winning wealth management advisory, investment banking and asset management expertise, or private and corporate banking services in Switzerland. \r\nWe\'re a team of more than 66,000 colleagues, collaborating across all major financial centers in 50 countries. We strive for excellence in everything we do, and this has awarded us recognition across our businesses. We offer a collaborative, international and diverse working environment that rewards passion, commitment and success – and are regularly recognized as an attractive employer.','310000','310100','333 South Huangpi Road, Huangpu District','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191111/8dc938ad8653e29cb830bcbcadabe276.jpg','Shanghai is the largest city in China by population. It is a global financial centre and transport hub, with the world\'s busiest container port. Located in the Yangtze River Delta, Shanghai has been described as the \"showpiece\" of the booming economy of mainland China renowned for its Lujiazui skyline, and museums and historic buildings, such as those along The Bund, as well as the City God Temple','<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Shanghai has 16 municipal districts with a total area of 6,340 square kilometers.Shanghai has a mild and humid climate, with a short spring and autumn. Usually, January is the coldest season with an average temperature of about 4℃, while July is usually the hottest with an average temperature of about 28℃.Shanghai is an important center of economy, transportation, science and technology, industry, finance, exhibition and shipping in China.</span></p>','2017-11-11','91520169ND7FGYND5F','瑞士银行有限公司','2018-11-11','2020