,(68,276,'The British School of Nanjing','',0,0,0,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191120/447c30de5e6721bddd7c29e46c15f41c.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191120/1b492bbc35d8b748569d2acaedaa58b3.mp4','','The British School of Nanjing is a Nord Anglia Education school and as such we provide our expat families a private education of the highest standard for their children between age 2 to 18 years old. The school is located south of Nanjing city, in a new and modern Mountain view campus. \r\n\r\nThe school follows the worldwide recognized English National Curriculum, also helps pupils to develop different set of skills through a variety of enrichment and extracurricular activities.  Our classroom teachers are highly qualified and receive up-to-date training to maintain the high standards. The small size classes and the low student teacher ratio ensures that pupils will get the full attention and personalized support they require to make an excellent academic and personal progress. \r\n\r\nWith a network of 61 NAE schools and over 61000 students across 28 countries, we feel that we can offer each and one of our pupils with unique opportunity beyond ordinary.','','','','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191120/c3413bd1218d6d1647a2017ba16069f9.jpg','Situated in the heartland of China’s Yanghtze River region, Nanjing is the capital city of China’s Jiangsu province. Nanjing (also popularly known as Ginling or Jinling) is the largest city in China’s eastern and southern regions, boasting a land mass of approximately 6,600 square kilometers. It is home to over 8.2 million people. The city occupies a prominent place in the country’s history and culture, having been the capital of numerous Chinese kingdoms, dynasties and republican governments. Situated at the heart of east China and Yangtze River Delta, the city is one of the largest inland ports in the world. It is also home to some of China’s best and high-quality universities such as Nanjing University. Moreover, it is among the country’s 4 great ancient cities and has consistently been one of the largest cities in the world for hundreds of years. It boasts several historical landscapes, numerous cultural facilities and key heritage sites that are well-known in the world over.','<p><em><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Whether you plan to visit Nanjing or you want to work in Nanjing, \r\nunderstanding the city can help you prepare for the life that waits you \r\nhere. This detailed guide of Nanjing city hopefully will give you virtually \r\neverything you may wish to know about this stunningly beautiful city. <br/></span></strong></em></em></p><p><em><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\"></span></strong></em></em></p><h2><strong><em>Overview of Nanjing</em></strong></h2><p><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Situated in \r\nthe heartland of China’s Yanghtze River region, Nanjing is the capital \r\ncity of China’s Jiangsu province. Nanjing (also popularly known as \r\nGinling or Jinling) is the largest city in China’s eastern and southern \r\nregions, boasting a land mass of approximately 6,600 square kilometers. \r\nIt is home to over 8.2 million people. The city occupies a prominent \r\nplace in the country’s history and culture, having been the capital of \r\nnumerous Chinese kingdoms, dynasties and republican governments. \r\nSituated at the heart of east China and Yangtze River Delta, the city is\r\n one of the largest inland ports in the world. It is also home to some \r\nof China’s best and high-quality universities such as Nanjing \r\nUniversity. Moreover, it is among the country’s 4 great ancient cities \r\nand has consistently been one of the largest cities in the world for \r\nhundreds of years. It boasts several historical landscapes, numerous \r\ncultural facilities and key heritage sites that are well-known in the \r\nworld over. <br/></span></strong></em></p><h2><em><strong>Neighborhoods/districts of Nanjing</strong></em></h2><p><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">As\r\n a sub-provincial city of Jiangsu province, Nanjing is sub-divided into \r\ndistricts. Here are some of the city’s most prominent districts.</span></strong></em></p><ul><li><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Xuanwu\r\n District-the urban district is located in the city’s north-eastern \r\narea. Moreover, it is home to Nanjing Municipal Government, in addition \r\nto being home to some of China’s finest attractions such as Hongwu \r\nEmperor’s Mausoleum , Xuanwu Lake and Nanjing International Exhibition \r\nCenter.</span></strong></em></li><li><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Baixia District-located along the Qinhuai River and \r\ncovering the city’s downtown areas, the district boasts a rich history \r\nand a long culture. Having benefited from massive infrastructural \r\ndevelopment over the past decade, the district is now an elegant living \r\nenvironment boasting a modern communication network and a world-class \r\ninfrastructure.</span></strong></em></li><li><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Gaochun District- It is the city’s southernmost \r\ndistrict, bordering Anhui province to the west and south. It is renowned\r\n for its traditional seafood and a vibrant nightlife.</span></strong></em></li><li><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Lishui \r\nDistrict-located in the city’s southern region and neighboring Gaochun \r\nDistrict to the north, Lishui is a fairly rural district though having a\r\n modern transportation network. It is also home to one of Nanjing’s \r\nbusiest railway stations- Lishui Station.</span></strong></em></li><li><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Pukou District-located\r\n in the city’s northwestern area, and between Chu River and Yangtze \r\nRiver, the district is home to many cultural heritages, natural \r\nlandscapes as well as numerous places of interest such as Forest Park \r\nand National Ancient Mountain Park.</span></strong></em></li></ul><p><em><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\"></span></strong></em></em></p><h2><em><strong>Getting in/out of Nanjing</strong></em></h2><p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><strong>International\r\n departures from the city as well as international arrivals to the city \r\nare mostly by air. The main airport that handles international arrivals \r\nand departures is Nanjing Lukou International Airport, which presently \r\nhas more than 130 air routes to over 20 international destinations and \r\n54 domestic destinations. There are numerous shuttle buses that ferry \r\ninternational visitors from the airport to various places throughout the\r\n city. Again, there are several buses operating between the airport and \r\nthe neighboring cities such as Huai’an, Shuyang and Yangzhong.</strong></span></p><h2><strong></strong><em><strong>Public Transportation in Nanjing</strong></em></h2><p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><em><strong>Getting around Nanjing has never been easier than now, thanks to the fact that Nanjing has a thoroughly developed transportation network characterized by high speed trains, subways and a superb road network. \r\nBelow are some of the common ways to get around the city. <br/></strong></em></span></p><h3><em><strong>Rail</strong></em></h3><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">Nanjing\r\n is a crucial railway hub in the entire East China. In fact, it serves \r\nas a meeting point of China’s east-west and north-south railway lines, \r\nall of which connect the country’s eastern, northern and middle regions.\r\n Train transport is the country’s most popular and convenient form of \r\ntransportation. Transportation is usually handled at all the city’s 17 \r\nrailway stations, with all of them operating partial and regular trains.\r\n With 5 hub stations, Nanjing South Railway station is renowned globally\r\n as the largest railway station in the whole of Asia. Rail transport is \r\none of the fastest ways of getting around Nanjing for both international\r\n visitors and locals. But if you would prefer moving around by train, it\r\n is important you book your ticket in advance and also know the right \r\nrailway station to board your train and the most convenient one to \r\nalight.</span></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><strong></strong></span></p><h3><em><strong>Subway</strong></em></h3><p><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">The city has a modern \r\nsubway system comprising of 7 subway lines, and there are also many \r\nsubway lines presently under construction. The subway has offered the \r\nfastest way of transportation for nearly a decade now. Better still, you\r\n can get to nearly anywhere you want to go by subway, provided you know \r\nthe right subway line to use. Again, buy your ticket from the right \r\nsubway station to avoid confusion. Most importantly, don’t throw away \r\nyour ticket because you may be asked to produce it at the next station.</span></strong></em></p><h3><em><strong>Long Distance Bus</strong></em></h3><p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><em><strong>This\r\n is the most preferred form of transportation for long distance \r\ntravelling. There are over 8 bus stations operating within all the \r\ndistricts and along the Nanjing –Shanghai Highway. Though using \r\nlong-distance buses can help you get around this city, particularly to \r\ndistance places, it is prudent you learn some Mandarin so that you can \r\ninteract effectively with the bus’ staff and also understand the entire \r\nroad signs on various roads. But the only drawback with using long-buses\r\n is that, most of them are congested thus compromising on your comfort \r\nduring your journeys. <br/></strong></em></span></p><h3><em><strong>Local Bus</strong></em></h3><p><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">The\r\n city has a bus transportation system that caters for those travelling \r\nwithin the city. The various buses operating in this city are more \r\nflexible compared to other forms of transportation, thanks to the fact \r\nthat they travel to all places within the city. Besides, fares are quite\r\n cheap and thus taking a city bus can help you tour the city \r\nconveniently and affordably.</span></strong></em></p><h3><em><strong>Taxi</strong></em></h3><p><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\">With\r\n over 20,999 taxis in Nanjing, the city has the highest number of taxis \r\ncompared to other big cities like Shanghai and Beijing. Most foreigners \r\nprefer taxis for moving from their hotels to the destinations of their \r\nchoice within the city. They are various types of taxis in the city \r\nnamely regular cars, British cars, mid-range cars and electric cars. \r\nHowever, touring the city by taxi may be a costly option for you just in\r\n case you are travelling far from the city. You can however bargain for \r\nreasonable rates by requesting the driver to charge you based on the \r\nnumber of kilometers you travel. That way, you can avoid being \r\novercharged by some unscrupulous drivers who take advantage of \r\nforeigners.</span></strong></em></p><p><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><strong><br/></strong></span></p><p><em><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px\"><br/></span></strong></em></em><br/></p><p><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191120/b944ae5eb2d024586d172b17a5ad9980.png\"/></p>',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','','',0,0,0,108,'2019-11-25 02:41:51','2019-11-20 08:53:04','2019-11-25 02:41:51'),(69,283,'Chamfond  Biotech Co.,Ltd','',0,0,0,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/d3f6b8d3d138e2c18735c7d1b1c0cb4a.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191122/3c6398288f5ba3c3231b60b18ea6294c.mp4','','Chinese name: 南京畅丰生物科技有限公司   Chamfond Biotech is a company that develops, manufactures and distributes innovative medical devices. We are committed to developing products which can fit into solutions for a broad range of applications which include Burn and plastic surgery, Microsurgery, Maxillofacial Surgery, Minimally Invasive Surgery, Pelvic Floor Repair Surgery and Tumor Intensive Care.','','','','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191120/60c1d2a60cf091779a6d8d6d241b44a1.png','Nanjing, the capital of Jiangsu Province, is situated in the golden Yangtze River Delta. The city plays an important role in the economy, transportation and education of the east part of China, and is said to be the second largest commercial port in the East China following Shanghai . With its majestic landscapes and epic history and cultures, it has become a hotspot for tourists who always fall in love with the city.','<p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Geography</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Nanjing occupies an area of about 6.6 thousand sq km. (1.6 million acres), with a opulation of more than 6 million. Known as one of China&#39;s &#39;Three Stoves&#39; (the others are Chongqing and Wuhan, Nanjing&#39;s temperatures in summer can reach a high of over 40 Celsius degree (104 F. degree) while the coldest days in winter can drop to less than minus 10 Celsius degree (14 F. degree). <br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>History</strong><br/>Nanjing is one of the best-known ancient capital cities in China and features a long history and deep cultures. The excavation of the skulls of ancient prehistoric men in the city dates Nanjing&#39;s civilization back to 350 thousand years ago. The city itself was built more than 2,400 years ago in the area southwest of the huge Zhonghua Gate. The gate was critical for many military functions. Since the third century AD, ten dynasties in China, including the epochal Republic of China founded by Sun Yat-sen, established Nanjing as their capital.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Attractions</strong><br/>Visitors to Nanjing will be delighted by the majestic scenery intertwined with many cultural antiquities. To the east is Mt. Zhongshan, also called Zijin (Purple Golden) Shan Scenic Area. The Mausoleum of Sun Yat-sen and in accordance with his last wishes, the later built Observatory are all located here. Besides, an imperial mausoleum - Ming Xiaoling Mausoleum and the attractive Linggu Temple were also built in the surrounding area. To the west of the mountain is the enthralling Mt. Qixia, the crimson autumn maple leaves of which always dazzle the eyes of visitors. The great Yangtze River traverses the northern part of the city and the spectacular scenery is best viewed from the railway &amp; highway Bridge. For travelers interested in the thousands of years&#39; history of the city, the Nanjing Museum features a large collection of relics and is worth a visit. There are also two ancient enticing lakes and classic gardens in the city that are renowned in the eastern part of China.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/ce12be24e87c69cad787eafed8c419c5.png\"/></span></p>',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','','',0,0,0,36,NULL,'2019-11-21 08:33:21','2019-12-03 07:30:39'),(70,284,'Seraphim Solar','',0,0,0,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/565502c9e3bdda81a6e04459c46e1e96.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/2866e3b2862821b13b7d65db48cee0a7.mp4','','Chinese name: 江苏赛拉弗光伏系统有限公司   As a world-class solar products manufacturer, Seraphim specializes in research, development, production, and sales of solar PV products. Since its foundation in 2011, Seraphim has accomplished significant achievements which outpaced most of our main competitors in terms of production capacity and in the number of innovative designs. Seraphim upholds its belief that innovation is the key driver behind advancement by pursuing new technologies and higher efficiencies. Seraphim is accredited as Batch I Smart Manufacturing Plant by Jiangsu Government, the Witness Laboratory Accreditation Certificate (WMTC) by CSA and TMP Laboratory Certificate by TUV SUD.','','','','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/53eea8cd8e4ea6cdb25686a2bafbc292.png','Changzhou is a prefecture-level city in southern Jiangsu province, China. It was previously known as Yanling, Lanling and Jinling. Located on the southern bank of the Yangtze River, Changzhou borders the provincial capital of Nanjing to the west, Zhenjiang to the northwest, Wuxi to the east, and the province of Zhejiang to the south. Changzhou is located in the highly developed Yangtze Delta region of China extending from Shanghai going northwest. The population of Changzhou city was 4,592,431 at the 2010 census.','<p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\">History</span></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">&quot;The Ruins of Yancheng&quot; (淹城遺址), comprise the remains of a walled city located in the Wujin district of Changzhou that was founded over 3000 years ago at the beginning of the Western Zhou dynasty. The earliest record of a settlement on the site of modern Changzhou is as a commandery founded in 221 BC at the beginning of the Qin Dynasty.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> <br/></span></span></span></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:18px\">Transportation</span></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">The first line of the Changzhou Metro opened on 21 September 2019.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></span><br/><span style=\"color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">Located just south of the Chang Jiang (Yangtze River), Changzhou station is situated on the original Beijing–Shanghai railway. Changzhou North station was completed in 2011 and is located in the north of Changzhou in the Xinbei district on the Beijing–Shanghai high-speed railway. Changzhou is also one of the main stops on the busy Shanghai–Nanjing intercity railway, with two stations located in Changzhou</span>.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/49cd673186a66160bc5979d65243dc6d.png\"/></span></p>',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','','',0,0,0,36,NULL,'2019-11-21 09:44:13','2019-12-03 07:27:44'),(71,285,'Wellington College Tianjin','',0,0,0,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/aaf711452b3af1d7cf32257b7aaa8265.jpg','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/d441c5cdaff7ad9fae57d4e938757351.mp4','','Opened in August 2011 in Tianjin, Wellington College International Tianjin is a vibrant and popular co-educational school offering top class British education for pupils aged 2-18 years.\r\n\r\nWellington College in Tianjin is at every level an extension of our partner school, Wellington College in the UK, a royal foundation, dating back over one hundred and fifty years. Our partnership is unique among British schools, the strengths and breadth of the links being unprecedented. \r\n\r\nThe Wellington campus offers the very best in educational facilities for our pupils, purpose-built, and incorporating everything required for academic and extra-curricular excellence in 21st-century schooling. They include state-of-the-art classrooms, science laboratories and art / design workshops, the College Library, dance studios, black box and at its heart, the College theatre and the Main Sports Centre and a variety of outdoor sports facilities.','','','','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/10af546e321da856614ed88fad9546d2.jpg','TIANJIN \r\nTianjin, neaning Port to Heavenly Capital is 130 kilometers southeast of Beijing, serving as Beijing\'s gateway to the Bohai Sea. China\'s third largest city with a population of 9,000,000, it is one of the three municipalities directly under the central government. Tianjin stands along the banks of the Haihe River and the bridges on the river, the neighbouring lakes, ponds and streams give this seaside city a distinctive quality.','<h1><em><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">Tianjin, China</span></strong></em></em></h1><p>Tianjin is the industrial and transport hub for Beijing and northern China. Sometimes you will still see it written as <span class=\"chW\">Tientsin WG</span>\r\n following the older spelling. Its position as one of the five \r\nmetropolitan provinces of China reflects its role as a city of \r\nimportance for many centuries. Its cosmopolitan feel has led it to be \r\ndubbed the `Shanghai` of the North’. It is famous for its seafood cuisine.</p><p><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191122/19d7877abe94d87617a64b6f59b43be7.jpg\"/><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span></strong></em><strong><em><br/></em></strong></p><p><strong><em></em></strong><em><strong><span style=\"font-size:24px\">Places to visit in Tianjin</span></strong></em></p><p>Tianjin is a bustling city rivaling <a href=\"http://undefined\" title=\"Vibrant city near mouth of the Yangzi\">Shanghai</a> and <a href=\"http://undefined\" title=\"Capital city of China since 1279\">Beijing</a>\r\n &nbsp;for the range of industries, shops, museums and cuisine available. The\r\n &nbsp;modern city is centered on these foreign concessions which have been \r\n&nbsp;restored while much of the old Chinese city has been replaced with \r\n&nbsp;modern buildings. Part of the old area is called The Five Avenues<a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\"><span></span></a> <span><span id=\"ch_wu_5-3\">五</span><span id=\"ch_da_big-4\">大</span><span id=\"ch_dao_road-5\">道</span></span> <span>Wudadao</span>.\r\n &nbsp;The distinctive architecture of old foreign concession buildings can \r\nbe &nbsp;seen there and the nationality of the original concessions is \r\nembodied &nbsp;in the style of the houses. Reflecting its colonial past there\r\n are two &nbsp;large cathedrals: Wang Hai Lou (north) and Xi Kai Jiao Tang \r\n(south).</p><h2><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191121/640224aeef451744175aa34bb8cac952.jpg\"/> <br/></h2><p>Of the older Chinese buildings in Tianjin the Ming Dynasty Dabei Monsatery<a href=\"http://undefined\" title=\"Important Chinese dynasty 1368-1644\"> </a>is a good example, as well as aGrand Mosque<a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\"><span></span></a>; Temple of Confucious and Tianhou Temple. A street has been recreated in the old style: <span><span id=\"ch_gu_ancient-6\">古</span><span id=\"ch_wen_script-7\">文</span><span id=\"ch_hua_to_make_into-8\">化</span><span id=\"ch_jie_street-9\">街</span></span> &nbsp;gǔ wén huà jiē ‘Ancient Culture Street’. There is a busy Antique Market &nbsp;on Shenyang Dao every day. More modern architecture can also be seen, &nbsp;Tianjin now has one of the largest Ferris wheels in the World : the Tianjin Eye.</p><h1><img src=\"https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191122/4b336dab8897aaa151134246247dbc5d.jpg\"/></h1><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br/><a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p><p><br/><a href=\"http://undefined\" target=\"_blank\"><span></span></a></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>',NULL,'','',NULL,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','','',0,0,0,108,NULL,'2019-11-21 10:41:03','2019-11-22 02:52:18'),(72,301,'Changzhou Institute of Technology','',0,0,0,'https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191122/29c906b8e1ca7b88619836d9c4acbc70.png','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191204/6262ac768c4a6e369217d35b8fa82e36.mp4','','Chinese name: 常州工学院   Changzhou Institute of Technology is a multidisciplinary and comprehensive university with 18 teaching units, offering 54 undergraduate programs with majors in fields such as Engineering, Science, Management, Economics, Literature, Education and Arts. There are more than 1100 staff members and around 15000 full-time students.','','','','https://uploads.100chinajobs.com/20191122/1de474c