text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><h3 class=\"h3_02\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 28px; margin: 0px; font-size: 16px; font-weight: normal; display: inline; background: url(&quot;https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/heading-h3.png&quot;) 3px 1px no-repeat;\">Transportation Hub of Greater Bay Area</h3></div><p style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 10px 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">Located in the west of<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); text-decoration: underline;\">Shenzhen</a>, Bao’an District is under the jurisdiction of Shenzhen. It borders<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); text-decoration: underline;\">Longhua District</a><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>on the east,<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); text-decoration: underline;\">Nanshan District</a><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>on the south, and<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); text-decoration: underline;\">Guangming District</a><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span>on the north. With strong economic strength, Bao’an District is the economic, industrial and export zone in Shenzhen. As a transportation hub of Guangdong-Hong Kong-Macao Greater Bay Area, Bao’an District has<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); text-decoration: underline;\">Shenzhen Bao&#39;an International Airport</a>, container ports and cargo terminals. Bao’an District Shenzhen is also a melting pot which is rich in tourist attractions. Among them, Shenzhen Phoenix Mountain Forest Park, Shenzhen Waterland Resort, Rock Lake, Zeng&#39;s Ancestral Hall &amp; Complex and Yangtai Mountain are worth visiting.</p><div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><div class=\"subTitle2017BG\" style=\"padding: 6px; margin: 15px 0px 0px; background: rgb(239, 239, 239);\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin: 0px; font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal; display: inline; background: url(&quot;https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/icon-title.png&quot;) 0px 2px no-repeat;\">Best Places to Visit &amp; Top Things to Do in Bao’an District</h2></div></div><div style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/logo/ico/hot2.gif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none;\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\"/>&nbsp;Shenzhen Phoenix Mountain（Fenghuang Mountain）<br/>Phoenix Mountain is on the east bank of the Pearl River, known as the “First Peak of Bao’an”. The whole spot consists of three parts: Wenchang Tower, Ancient Temple and the sunset glow scenic area. While climbing the mountain, travelers can view the beautiful natural scenery, strange rocks, and visit historical relics in the temple, and then enjoy the sunset after climbing to the top.<br/><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/logo/ico/hot2.gif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none;\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\"/>&nbsp;Rock Lake Resort<br/>It is famous for its unique natural hot springs. The buildings are in Spanish style and the environment is quiet. With well-equipment facilities, travelers can not only experience the wonderful hot springs, but also taste local food, ride horses and watch fireworks performance.<br/><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/logo/ico/hot2.gif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none;\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\"/>&nbsp;Yangtai Mountain<br/>It is one of the eight scenic spots in Shenzhen and famous for its waterfall. The flowers are in full bloom in spring, and the summer is cool which makes it a good summer resort. On top of the mountain, you can overlook the scenery of Rock Lake. The Hiking Festival held on 9th September in Yangtai Mountain attracts many travelers.<br/><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.travelchinaguide.com/images/logo/ico/hot2.gif\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border: none;\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\"/>&nbsp;Zeng&#39;s Ancestral Hall &amp; Complex<br/>Located in Bao’an District, it is an ancestral building which is a place to worship ancestors of the Zeng Family. With greater influence and historical value, it represents the excellent cultural form of ancestral beliefs in Hakka culture. Travelers can visit the whole ancestral hall with the stone arch, and the granite stone architecture-the Stone Archway, and also enjoy the beautiful scenery and rich history.</div><div class=\"subTitle2017BG\" style=\"padding: 6px; margin: 15px 0px 0px; background: rgb(239, 239, 239); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><h2 class=\"h2_01\" style=\"padding: 0px 0px 0px 25px; margin: 0px; font-size: 18px; font-weight: normal; display: inline; background: url(&quot;https://data.travelchinaguide.com/images/background/icon/icon-title.png&quot;) 0px 2px no-repeat;\">Transportation</h2></div><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: justify; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">Shenzhen Bao’an International Airport is about 15 km (9.3 mi) from the central district, travelers can take<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></span><a href=\"http://undefined\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: rgb(51, 102, 204); text-decoration: underline; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-s