charlbotha39@gmail.com','unknown','86','unknown','','live:charlbotha39_1','<p><span style=\"font-size:19px\">Dear Director,</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:19px\">I believe I was born with an innate desire for experiencing the world and sharing knowledge with others. I have a bachelor’s degree in Marketing and am a connoisseur of the English language. Since I can remember, I have loved the way words came together to express ideas and feelings. I</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:19px\">am seeking to teach in a diverse environment where I can impact and motivate students to use the English language.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:19px\">A successful teacher is driven by results while understanding the needs of her classroom. Successful teachers create thriving, interactive classrooms. A successful teacher has mastered her subject material and begins each day with a focused yet diverse lesson plan. I will use a variety of audio, visual and tangible resources. I will encourage students by having relevant, relatable material. I will facilitate learning by maintaining a no-judgment classroom where students are excited to give ideas and have a native English speaker answer their questions.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:19px\">In my employment, I worked directly with native people in some of countries. This taught about geography and most importantly, the power of the English language on a global scale. Speaking English can take one&#39;s life to the next level. Every day as a correspondent, I experienced the use of proper English grammar and the fun of teaching others to hold an interview or conversation. As a volunteer, I enjoyed being in a classroom and giving back to society. My favorite childhood hobby was storytelling, which taught me to use pitch and tone to capture an audience through words. Endless years of drama and acting made me comfortable speaking in front of crowds.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size:19px\">Please take a moment to look