 of Toronto&#39;s TEFL Certificate. I also have a Bachelor of Arts in Philosophy and History from Western University.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>I have previously taught ESL in Korea, Japan, and Alberta. My teaching experience in Busan was mostly to university students focusing on conversation skills. I taught at a few different schools in Tokyo. In Shinjuku I tailored lessons to the student needs as assessed by myself and other staff members. In Jujo I taught all ages from prekindergarten to adults. I enjoyed teaching children the most. I also worked as a teacher evaluator for Benesse in Tokyo. This position required me to visit various home schools, and complete narrative assessments of the Japanese born English teachers, and to model a sample lesson as a guest instructor to the children.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>For about eight years I worked in post-secondary institutions as an Academic Advisor. As an Academic Advisor I proved myself an able communicator while assisting students with a variety of complex issues at all points of their journey from prospective student to graduate. Daily, I helped students navigate the sometimes arcane university policies and processes by interpreting in plain language the real functional impact on them and their goals. To be successful, I needed to introduce the relevant information and advice in a timely, contextual, and intuitive matter.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>I have excellent written and spoken communication skills and was published more than twenty times in Canadian newspapers in my mid-twenties. I have provided a link to them in my resume. This year I am traveling, writing, and currently caring for my grandma in Mt Brydges, Canada.</span></p><p><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span>Sincerely,</span></p><p><br/></p>',2,'',1,'','','',1,0,'',0,'',0,0,0,0,'',0,'',NULL,NULL,1,0,6,1,35,NULL,'2019-12-02 01:32:54','2019-12-02 01:32:54'),(306,461,0,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,'https://uploads.